.TH "blk_integrity_register" 9 "blk_integrity_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blk_integrity_register \- Register a gendisk as being integrity-capable
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" blk_integrity_register
.BI "(struct gendisk *disk "  ","
.BI "struct blk_integrity *template "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "disk" 12
struct gendisk pointer to make integrity-aware
.IP "template" 12
block integrity profile to register
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
When a device needs to advertise itself as being able to
send/receive integrity metadata it must use this function to register
the capability with the block layer. The template is a blk_integrity
struct with values appropriate for the underlying hardware. See
Documentation/block/data-integrity.rst.
